Package science.aist.machinelearning.core.fitness

Interface CachetEvaluator<GT,​PT>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AmalgamEvaluationCachet, AmalgamGenerationCachet, ElementEqualityCachet, GPDepthCachet, GPEvaluationAbortingTimerCachet, GPEvaluationCachet, GPEvaluationLimitCreatorCachet, GPEvaluationTimerCachet, GPNodeCostCachet, GPRuntimeCachet, GPRuntimeFromEvaluationCachet, GPSolutionCachet, PreferACachet, PreferTCachet
    public interface CachetEvaluator<GT,​PT>
    A CachetEvaluator determines a single quality characteristic on a Solution and will be used by the Evaluator. It needs to be implemented specifically for the needs of a given machine learning problem
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Oliver Krauss

    • Method Detail

      • evaluateQuality

        double evaluateQuality​(Solution<GT,​PT> solution)
        Evaluates a solutions quality. The closer to 0 a mapping is the better it is. Adds a {} to a Solution that determines the quality of a single constraint.
        Parameters:
        solution - to be evaluated
        Returns:
        quality between 0 (best) and infinite

      • getName

        String getName()
        Defines the name of this cachet, for use in the Evaluator identity. All Cachets generated by this evaluator WILL receive this as cachet.setName() Note that the name should be universally unique (so a version number in this does make sense!)
        Returns:
        name
